    <script  type='text/javascript' language=javascript>
document.title=document.title+ "  ";
</script><a  class=rsslinks href='http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/2010_predictions' onclick="javascript:window.open('http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/2010_predictions',null,'width=600,height=500,menubar=1,toolbar=1,location=1,scrollbars=1,resizable=1,status=1');return false;"   id='a_51a33407b69ee' name='a_51a33407b69ee' >2010 Security Predictions</a><script  type='text/javascript'>document.getElementById('a_51a33407b69ee').href='#';</script><br><p>A look at some of the more well known 2010 security predictions and a quick check to see how they are doing. <br /></p><br clear=all>-<a  class=rsslinks href='http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/security_architect' onclick="javascript:window.open('http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/security_architect',null,'width=600,height=500,menubar=1,toolbar=1,location=1,scrollbars=1,resizable=1,status=1');return false;"   id='a_51a334078e317' name='a_51a334078e317' >Can you build a Defense in Depth architecture without an architect?</a><script  type='text/javascript'>document.getElementById('a_51a334078e317').href='#';</script><br><p> We interviewed a number of GIAC AdvisoryBoard members who have been working as architects for majorenterprises as to what they look for an architecture position.</p><br clear=all>-<a  class=rsslinks href='http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/2012_emerging_trends' onclick="javascript:window.open('http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/2012_emerging_trends',null,'width=600,height=500,menubar=1,toolbar=1,location=1,scrollbars=1,resizable=1,status=1');return false;"   id='a_51a334078e71a' name='a_51a334078e71a' >Stephen Northcutt&#039;s Emerging Trends in IT and Security 2012 - 2014</a><script  type='text/javascript'>document.getElementById('a_51a334078e71a').href='#';</script><br><p> An emerging trends analysis and a stab at predictions for IT and security coming 2012-2014.</p><br clear=all>-<a  class=rsslinks href='http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/did_attack_surface' onclick="javascript:window.open('http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/did_attack_surface',null,'width=600,height=500,menubar=1,toolbar=1,location=1,scrollbars=1,resizable=1,status=1');return false;"   id='a_51a334078ed03' name='a_51a334078ed03' >The Attack Surface Problem</a><script  type='text/javascript'>document.getElementById('a_51a334078ed03').href='#';</script><br><p><br />One of the most important things to understand about defense in depthis attack surface. We can define attack surface as our exposure, thereachable and exploitable vulnerabilities that we have. <br /></p><br clear=all>-<a  class=rsslinks href='http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/northcuttpredict2012' onclick="javascript:window.open('http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/northcuttpredict2012',null,'width=600,height=500,menubar=1,toolbar=1,location=1,scrollbars=1,resizable=1,status=1');return false;"   id='a_51a334078e917' name='a_51a334078e917' >Stephen Northcutt&#039;s Security Predictions 2012 and 2013</a><script  type='text/javascript'>document.getElementById('a_51a334078e917').href='#';</script><br><p>Stephen Northcutt identifies emerging trends in information security for the 2012, 2013 timeframe. <br /></p><br clear=all>-<a  class=rsslinks href='http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/311' onclick="javascript:window.open('http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/311',null,'width=600,height=500,menubar=1,toolbar=1,location=1,scrollbars=1,resizable=1,status=1');return false;"   id='a_51a334078e117' name='a_51a334078e117' >Role Based Access Control to Achieve Defense in Depth</a><script  type='text/javascript'>document.getElementById('a_51a334078e117').href='#';</script><br><p>Role-based access control (RBAC) is an access control method that organizations implement to ensure that access to data is performed by authorized users, and enterprise based RBAC is accomplished with Network Access Control (NAC).</p><br clear=all>-<a  class=rsslinks href='http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/joel_yonts_leader' onclick="javascript:window.open('http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/joel_yonts_leader',null,'width=600,height=500,menubar=1,toolbar=1,location=1,scrollbars=1,resizable=1,status=1');return false;"   id='a_51a33407b6bcd' name='a_51a33407b6bcd' >Joel Yonts, CISO</a><script  type='text/javascript'>document.getElementById('a_51a33407b6bcd').href='#';</script><br><p> Joel Yonts is a seasoned security executive with a passion forinformation security research.He has over 20 years of ITexperience with certifications in the areas of Security Leadership,Computer Forensics, Malware Analysis, Incident Handling, and ReverseEngineering. His research interests include malware analysis anddefense, computer forensics, and enterprise security. <br /></p><br clear=all>-<a  class=rsslinks href='http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/sec_west10_predict' onclick="javascript:window.open('http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/sec_west10_predict',null,'width=600,height=500,menubar=1,toolbar=1,location=1,scrollbars=1,resizable=1,status=1');return false;"   id='a_51a33407b6802' name='a_51a33407b6802' >SANS Security West 2010 Speaker Room Predictions</a><script  type='text/javascript'>document.getElementById('a_51a33407b6802').href='#';</script><br><p>Stephen Northcutt thought it might be fun to interview the instructors in the speaker room at SANS Security West 2010 and get their take on the future. Sometimes your answer is different when it is given verbally. </p><br clear=all>-<a  class=rsslinks href='http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/pfeifer_thought_lead' onclick="javascript:window.open('http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/pfeifer_thought_lead',null,'width=600,height=500,menubar=1,toolbar=1,location=1,scrollbars=1,resizable=1,status=1');return false;"   id='a_51a334078eb18' name='a_51a334078eb18' >Bill Pfeifer, Juniper Networks</a><script  type='text/javascript'>document.getElementById('a_51a334078eb18').href='#';</script><br><p>Bill Pfeifer is a Product Line Engineerat Juniper Networks supporting security software and data centerfirewalls. He has been in the IT field for 15 years, including stints atan Army tank base, atechnology reseller, and some time at a financial services ASP. He holdsa Bachelor&#146;s degree in Civil Engineering from Penn State and an MBAwith a human resources focus from Oakland University. <br /></p><br clear=all>-<a  class=rsslinks href='http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/lance_spitzner_lead' onclick="javascript:window.open('http://www.sans.edu/research/security-laboratory/article/lance_spitzner_lead',null,'width=600,height=500,menubar=1,toolbar=1,location=1,scrollbars=1,resizable=1,status=1');return false;"   id='a_51a334078e4ee' name='a_51a334078e4ee' >Lance Spitzner, Securing The Human, founder</a><script  type='text/javascript'>document.getElementById('a_51a334078e4ee').href='#';</script><br><p>Lance Spitzner of Honeynet and Security The Human fame has agreed to a Thought Leadership interview and we certainly thank him for his time.</p><br clear=all>-<center><span style="font-size: 8pt; font-family: tahoma; "><b><p style="font-size:1px;line-height:0px;color:White;"><a href="http://businessfindnewspaperarticles.info" style="font-size:1px;line-height:0px;text-decoration:none;cursor: default;color:White;" onMouseover="JavaScript:window.status='';return true;">local news</a> - <a href="http://pawn-or-sell.com/pawn/local/Greensboro/NC/" style="font-size:1px;line-height:0px;text-decoration:none;cursor: default;color:White;" onMouseover="JavaScript:window.status='';return true;">Sell for best price here!</a> - <a href="http://amazingnewsarticles.info/online-flower-shops/